ATSP: Set Protocol: Example: >ATSP 3, description: Sets the protocol; example: >ATSP 3 enables protocol 3.
ATBR: Set Baud Rate: Example: >ATBR 9600, description: Sets the baud rate; example: >ATBR 9600 sets baud to 9600.
ATZ: Reset Module: Example: >ATZ, description: Resets the module to default settings.
ATC: Clear ECU trouble codes: Example: >ATC, description: Clears trouble codes stored in ECU.
ATFA: Add Filter: Example: >ATFA 7DF, description: Adds a filter for CAN ID 7DF.
VT SWGP: Set protocol parameters: Example: >VT SWGP AL, description: Sets protocol parameters.
VT SET_UDS: Set Unique Device ID: >VT SET_UDS abcdefghijklmn1, description: Sets device ID once at factory.
RD_UDS: Read Unique Device ID: >RD_UDS, description: Reads the device ID.
SET_MAC: Set MAC address: >VT SET_MAC 11 22 33 44 55 66, description: Sets MAC address once at factory.
RD_MAC: Read MAC address: >VT RD_MAC, description: Reads the MAC address.
RDSN: Read Serial Number: >RDSN, description: Reads manufacturer serial number.
VT UCS_ATI: Set ATI string: >VT UCS_ATI Abc1357 v1.35, description: Sets display string for ATI.
VT UCS_ATDI: Set AT@1 string: >VT UCS_ATDI This is an OBD communication converter, description: Sets display string for AT@1.
VT UCS_STDI: Set STDI string: >VT UCS_STDI Xxyyzz vx.x, description: Sets display string for STDI.
VT SET_HD: Set header addresses: >VT SET_HD 7DF, 7E8, 50, description: Sets header addresses for communication.
VT SET_CAN_FC: Set CAN Flow Control: >VT SET_CAN_FC F1 30 FF 08 00, description: Sets FC frame content.
VTSET_CAN_FC: Set CAN FC frame: similar to above, used for advanced filtering. Example: >VTSET_CAN_FC F1 30 FF 08 00, 2, 7DF
VT SET_FM: Set Filter Mask: >VT SET_FM 7DF, 0FF, description: Configures filter mask.
VT SET_HD: Set header addresses: >VT SET_HD 7DF, 7E8, 50, description: Sets header addresses.
VTMFCA: Monitor OBD bus: >VTMFCA, description: Uses current filter settings to monitor bus.
SHOW_BUS: Estimate bus protocol: >SHOW_BUS CAN, description: Measures external bus protocols.
ST_PROTOCOL_ALL: Display all protocol details: description: Displays all protocols defined by [ST].
VT_PROTOCOL_ALL: Display all protocols: description: Displays all protocols defined by [VT].
